FBIS3-50515 "drlat002_g_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-002 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Jan 1994 CENTRAL AMERICA Guatemala Army Spokesperson Hints of URNG Role in Mexican Rebellion PA0301211394 Guatemala City Teleonce Television in Spanish 1900 GMT 3 Jan 94 PA0301211394 Guatemala City Teleonce Television Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From the "Telepress" newscast] [Text] The Guatemalan Army does not yet have official information on the armed rebellion in Chiapas State, Mexico. Edith Vargas de Marroquin, spokesperson for the Army Information and Press Department, [words indistinct] and added that the participation of the Guatemalan National Revolutionary Unity [URNG] in this movement: [Begin recording] [Marroquin] The Guatemalan Army does not yet have an official report [words indistinct] Mexican Government. The Foreign Ministry and the Mexican Embassy in this country will [words indistinct]. The Army is maintaining its security along the Mexican border and other border areas [words indistinct]. [Unidentified reporter] [Words indistinct] [Marroquin] For the time being there is no [word indistinct] situation. [Reporter] [Words indistinct] [Marroquin] We are maintaining communications [words indistinct] with the Mexican Army [words indistinct]. [Reporter] [Words indistinct]? [Marroquin] We learned about that through the media; as I said, we do not have an official report or an official version of the (?incident). The information we have was obtained through the media. [Reporter] [Words indistinct] [Marroquin] We think that it could be that the URNG, given the (?warmongering position) it has maintained for so long, is somehow participating in this regretful situation [words indistinct] many high-caliber weapons were seized. It could be inferred that they were not only to arm URNG members but to arm a clandestine (?group). This arms cache was accidentally discovered [words indistinct] other caches. [end recording]
